******
[1] Global as of 23 Feb 2022 - GPEI/WHO WPV1 (AFP Malawi), cVDPV1 (AFP Madagascar), cVDPV2 (AFP DR Congo, Nigeria, Yemen)
Date: Thu 24 Feb 2022
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO
https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update 23 Feb 2022, World Health Organization
---------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 1
Environment: 0
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 10
Environment: 14
Others: 4

Headlines
---------
- After the safe and successful rollout of nationwide polio campaigns since November 2021, we have received tragic news that 8 health workers at the forefront have been killed this morning in a series of shootings in Takhar and Kunduz in northeast Afghanistan. The vaccination campaign has been suspended in both provinces. A statement has been issued by the Regional Director of WHO's Eastern Mediterranean Region, Dr Ahmed Al-Mandhari, as well as by the United Nations in the country, condemning these attacks, expressing condolences to the families and underscoring that the provision of health and the safety of health workers at the forefront are paramount, and must be kept neutral to any geo-political situation anywhere.

Our thoughts and prayers are both with the families and our teams on the ground at this time. [See section 2 below]

- Last week, Malawi reported a WPV1 case in a 3-year-old girl in the capital, Lilongwe. Analysis shows that the virus is genetically linked to WPV1 that was detected in Pakistan's Sindh province in October 2019. This is the first WPV1 case from the continent of Africa in over 5 years.

Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- DR Congo: 2 cVDPV2 cases
- Madagascar: 2 cVDPV1 cases and 6 cVDPV1 positive environmental samples
- Malawi: 1 WPV1 case
- Nigeria: 3 cVDPV2 cases and 8 positive environmental samples
- Yemen: 3 cVDPV2 cases

Afghanistan
• No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. There is 1 WPV1 case reported in 2022 and 4 in 2021. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 43.

Pakistan
• No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. The total number of WPV1 cases in 2021 remains 1. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 8.

Benin
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021.

Burkina Faso
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Cameroon
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021.

Central African Republic
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Chad
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Congo (Republic of)
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Côte d'Ivoire
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no reported cases in 2021.

Djibouti
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week. There are 5 positive environmental samples reported in the country, linked to the virus circulating in Yemen.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
• 2 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported in Maniema 1 case being the first of 2022 and the other is from 2021. The number of 2021 cases now stand at 26.

Egypt
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 11 positive samples reported in 2021.

Ethiopia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 10 cases reported in 2021.

Gambia
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week. There are 9 positive samples reported in 2021.

Ghana
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Guinea
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021.

Guinea-Bissau
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in the country which are linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria in 2021.

Kenya
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples reported, 1 in 2020 and 1 in 2021. The viruses are linked to the Banadir outbreak in Somalia.

Liberia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in the country in 2021.

Madagascar
• 2 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported; 1 each in Diana and Sofia 1 being the first of 2022 and the other is from 2021. The number of 2021 cases now stand at 12.
• 6 cVDPV1 positive environmental samples were reported; 3 in Analamanga, 1 in Diana and 2 in Sofia.

Malawi
• 1 WPV1 reported this week in Central making it the first WPV1 case in the country in 2021 and in the continent since 2016.

Mali
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Mauritania
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 6 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in 2021.

Mozambique
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Niger
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains at 15.

Nigeria
• 3 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 2 in Borno and 1 in Kano which is the first of 2022. The number of 2021 cases now stands at 415.
• 8 positive environmental samples were reported; 1 each in Borno, Gombe, Jigawa and Kano and 4 in Katsina.

Senegal
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 17 cases reported in 2021.

Sierra Leone
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 5 cases in 2021.

Somalia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case in 2022 and 1 case in 2021.

South Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 9 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2021.

Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Tajikistan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 32 cases reported in 2021.

Togo
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Uganda
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad reported in 2021.

Ukraine
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Yemen
• 3 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 1 each in Abyan, Aldhale and Alhudaidah. There are 13 cVDPV2 cases and 3 cVDPV1 cases reported in 2021.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 22 Feb 2022
Wild poliovirus (WPV)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2022: 1 (compared with 2 for the same period in 2021)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 6

Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2022: 4 (compared with 9 for the same period in 2021)
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 635

